Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone.

Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board and cut into chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the pepper and onion and stir-fry until just soft, ~{4-5%mins}.

Turn the heat down to medium, then add the garlic and @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the black beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water for the sauce{50%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @soured cream{75%g} and lime zest. Set your zesty soured cream aside.

When the fajita mix is ready, squeeze in some lime juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When everything's ready, share the wedges between your plates and top with the fajita mix.

Scatter the cheese and avocado all over. Finish with a big dollop of the zesty soured cream - wedges loaded!

Serve with any remaining lime cut into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!